261 string Feat::get_eqn(bool sort, Individual& ind)
262 {
263  vector<string> features = ind.get_features();
264  vector<float> weights = ind.ml->get_weights();
265  float offset = ind.ml->get_bias();
266 
267  /* if (params.normalize) */
268  /* { */
269  /* offset = this->N.adjust_offset(weights, offset); */
270  /* this->N.adjust_weights(weights); */
271  /* } */
272 
273  vector<size_t> order(weights.size());
274  if (sort)
275  {
276  vector<float> aweights(weights.size());
277  for (int i =0; i<aweights.size(); ++i)
278  aweights[i] = fabs(weights[i]);
279  order = argsort(aweights, false);
280  }
281  else
282  iota(order.begin(), order.end(), 0);
283 
284  string output;
285  output += to_string(offset);
286 
287  if (weights.size() > 0)
288  if (weights.at(0) > 0)
289  output+= "+";
290  int i = 0;
291  for (const auto& o : order)
292  {
293  output += to_string(weights.at(o), 2);
294  output += "*";
295  output += features.at(o);
296  if (i < order.size()-1)
297  {
298  if (weights.at(i+1) > 0)
299  output+= "+";
300  }
301  ++i;
302  }
303 
304  return output;
305 }

357 string Feat::get_archive(bool front)
358 {
359  /* TODO: maybe this should just return the to_json call of
360  * the underlying population / archive. I guess the problem
361  * is that we don't have to_json defined for vector<Individual>.
362  */
363  vector<Individual>* printed_pop = NULL;
364 
365  string r = "";
366 
367  vector<size_t> idx;
368  bool subset = false;
369  if (front) // only return individuals on the Pareto front
370  {
371  if (use_arch)
372  {
373  printed_pop = &archive.individuals;
374  }
375  else
376  {
377  unsigned n = 1;
378  subset = true;
379  idx = this->pop.sorted_front(n);
380  printed_pop = &this->pop.individuals;
381  }
382  }
383  else
384  printed_pop = &this->pop.individuals;
385 
386  if (!subset)
387  {
388  idx.resize(printed_pop->size());
389  std::iota(idx.begin(), idx.end(), 0);
390  }
391 
392  bool includes_best_ind = false;
393 
394  for (int i = 0; i < idx.size(); ++i)
395  {
396  Individual& ind = printed_pop->at(idx[i]);
397 
398  json j;
399  to_json(j, ind);
400 
401  r += j.dump();
402 
403  if (i < idx.size() -1)
404  r += "\n";
405  // check if best_ind is in here
406  if (ind.id == best_ind.id)
407  includes_best_ind = true;
408  }
409 
410  // add best_ind, if it is not included
411  if (!includes_best_ind)
412  {
413  r += "\n";
414  json j;
415  to_json(j, best_ind);
416  r += j.dump();
417  }
418 
419  r += "\n";
420  // delete pop pointer
421  printed_pop = NULL;
422  delete printed_pop;
423 
424  return r;
425 }

483 void Feat::fit(MatrixXf& X, VectorXf& y,
484  LongData Z)
485 {
486 
507  // start the clock
508  timer.Reset();
509  r.set_seed(this->random_state);
510  // signal handler
511  signal(SIGINT, my_handler);
512  // reset statistics
513  this->stats = Log_Stats();
514  params.use_batch = params.bp.batch_size>0;
515 
516  string FEAT;
517  if (params.verbosity == 1)
518  {
519  FEAT = (
520  "/// Feature Engineering Automation Tool "
521  "* \xc2\xa9 La Cava et al 2017 "
522  "* GPL3 \\\\\\\n"
523  );
524  }
525  else if (params.verbosity == 2)
526  {
527  FEAT = (
528  "/////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////\n"
529  "// * Feature Engineering Automation Tool * //\n"
530  "// La Cava et al. 2017 //\n"
531  "// License: GPL v3 //\n"
532  "// https://cavalab.org/feat //\n"
533  "/////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////\n"
534  );
535  }
536  logger.log(FEAT,1);
537 
538  if (params.use_batch)
539  {
540  if (params.bp.batch_size >= X.cols())
541  {
542  logger.log("turning off batch because X has fewer than "
543  + to_string(params.bp.batch_size) + " samples", 1);
544  params.use_batch = false;
545  }
546  else
547  {
548  logger.log("using batch with batch_size= "
549  + to_string(params.bp.batch_size), 2);
550  }
551  }
552  std::ofstream log;
553  if (!logfile.empty())
554  log.open(logfile, std::ofstream::app);
555 
556  if(str_dim.compare("") != 0)
557  {
558  string dimension;
559  dimension = str_dim.substr(0, str_dim.length() - 1);
560  logger.log("STR DIM IS "+ dimension, 2);
561  logger.log("Cols are " + std::to_string(X.rows()), 2);
562  logger.log("Setting dimensionality as " +
563  std::to_string((int)(ceil(stod(dimension)*X.rows()))), 2);
564  set_max_dim(ceil(stod(dimension)*X.rows()));
565  }
566 
567  params.init(X, y);
568 
569  this->archive.set_objectives(params.objectives);
570 
571  // normalize data
572  if (params.normalize)
573  N.fit_normalize(X,params.dtypes);
574  this->pop = Population(params.pop_size);
575  this->evaluator = Evaluation(params.scorer_);
576 
577  /* create an archive to save Pareto front,
578  * unless NSGA-2 is being used for survival
579  */
580  /* if (!survival.compare("nsga2")) */
581  /* use_arch = false; */
582  /* else */
583  /* use_arch = true; */
584  use_arch = false;
585 
586  logger.log("scorer: " + params.scorer_, 1);
587 
588  // split data into training and test sets
589  //Data data(X, y, Z, params.classification);
590  DataRef d(X, y, Z, params.classification, params.protected_groups);
591  //DataRef d;
592  //d.setOriginalData(&data);
593  d.train_test_split(params.shuffle, params.split);
594  // define terminals based on size of X
595  params.set_terminals(d.o->X.rows(), d.o->Z);
596 
597  // initial model on raw input
598  logger.log("Setting up data", 2);
599  float t0 = timer.Elapsed().count();
600 
601  //data for batch training
602  MatrixXf Xb;
603  VectorXf yb;
604  LongData Zb;
605  Data db(Xb, yb, Zb, params.classification, params.protected_groups);
606 
607  Data *tmp_train;
608 
609  if(params.use_batch)
610  {
611  tmp_train = d.t;
612  d.t->get_batch(db, params.bp.batch_size);
613  d.setTrainingData(&db);
614  }
615 
616  if (params.classification)
617  params.set_sample_weights(d.t->y);
618 
619 
620  // initialize population
622  logger.log("Initializing population", 2);
623 
624  bool random = selector.get_type() == "random";
625 
626  // initial model
628  logger.log("Fitting initial model", 2);
629  t0 = timer.Elapsed().count();
630  initial_model(d);
631  logger.log("Initial fitting took "
632  + std::to_string(timer.Elapsed().count() - t0) + " seconds",2);
633 
634  // initialize population with initial model and/or starting pop
635  pop.init(best_ind,params,random, this->starting_pop);
636  logger.log("Initial population:\n"+pop.print_eqns(),3);
637 
638  // evaluate initial population
639  logger.log("Evaluating initial population",2);
640  evaluator.fitness(pop.individuals,*d.t,params);
641  evaluator.validation(pop.individuals,*d.v,params);
642 
643  logger.log("Initial population done",2);
644  logger.log(std::to_string(timer.Elapsed().count()) + " seconds",2);
645 
646  vector<size_t> survivors;
647 
648  if(params.use_batch) // reset d to all training data
649  d.setTrainingData(tmp_train, true);
650 
651  // =====================
652  // main generational loop
653  unsigned g = 0;
654  unsigned stall_count = 0;
655  float fraction = 0;
656  // continue until max gens is reached or max_time is up (if it is set)
657 
658  while(
659  // time limit
660  (params.max_time == -1 || params.max_time > timer.Elapsed().count())
661  // generation limit
662  && g<params.gens
663  // stall limit
664  && (params.max_stall == 0 || stall_count < params.max_stall)
665  )
666  {
667  fraction = params.max_time == -1 ? ((g+1)*1.0)/params.gens :
668  timer.Elapsed().count()/params.max_time;
669  if(params.use_batch)
670  {
671  d.t->get_batch(db, params.bp.batch_size);
672  DataRef dbr; // reference to minibatch data
673  dbr.setTrainingData(&db);
674  dbr.setValidationData(d.v);
675 
676  if (params.classification)
677  params.set_sample_weights(dbr.t->y);
678 
679  run_generation(g, survivors, dbr, log, fraction, stall_count);
680  }
681  else
682  {
683  run_generation(g, survivors, d, log, fraction, stall_count);
684  }
685 
686  g++;
687  }
688  // =====================
689  if ( params.max_stall != 0 && stall_count >= params.max_stall)
690  logger.log("learning stalled",2);
691  else if ( g >= params.gens)
692  logger.log("generation limit reached",2);
693  else
694  logger.log("max time reached",2);
695 
696  logger.log("train score: " + std::to_string(this->min_loss), 2);
697  logger.log("validation score: " + std::to_string(min_loss_v), 2);
698  logger.log("fitting final model to all training data...",2);
699 
700 
701  // simplify the final model
702  if (simplify > 0.0)
703  {
704  this->best_ind.fit(*d.o, params);
705  simplify_model(d, this->best_ind);
706  }
707 
708  // fit final model to best features
709  final_model(d);
710 
711  // if we're not using an archive, let's store the final population in the
712  // archive
713  if (!use_arch)
714  {
715  archive.individuals = pop.individuals;
716  }
717 
718  if (save_pop > 0)
719  {
720  pop.save(this->logfile+".pop.gen" + to_string(params.current_gen)
721  + ".json");
722  this->best_ind.save(this->logfile+".best.json");
723  }
724 
725  if (log.is_open())
726  log.close();
727 
728  this->fitted = true;
729  logger.log("Run Completed. Total time taken is "
730  + std::to_string(timer.Elapsed().count()) + " seconds", 1);
731  logger.log("best model: " + this->get_eqn(),1);
732  logger.log("tabular model:\n" + this->get_model(),2);
733  logger.log("/// ----------------------------------------------------------------- \\\\\\",
734  1);
735 
736 }

738 void Feat::run_generation(unsigned int g,
739  vector<size_t> survivors,
740  DataRef &d,
741  std::ofstream &log,
742  float fraction,
743  unsigned& stall_count)
744 {
745  d.t->set_protected_groups();
746 
747  params.set_current_gen(g);
748 
749  // select parents
750  logger.log("selection..", 2);
751  vector<size_t> parents = selector.select(pop, params, *d.t);
752  logger.log("parents:\n"+pop.print_eqns(), 3);
753 
754  // variation to produce offspring
755  logger.log("variation...", 2);
756  variator.vary(pop, parents, params,*d.t);
757  logger.log("offspring:\n" + pop.print_eqns(true), 3);
758 
759  // evaluate offspring
760  logger.log("evaluating offspring...", 2);
761  evaluator.fitness(pop.individuals, *d.t, params, true);
762  evaluator.validation(pop.individuals, *d.v, params, true);
763 
764  // select survivors from combined pool of parents and offspring
765  logger.log("survival...", 2);
766  survivors = survivor.survive(pop, params, *d.t);
767 
768  // reduce population to survivors
769  logger.log("shrinking pop to survivors...",2);
770  pop.update(survivors);
771  logger.log("survivors:\n" + pop.print_eqns(), 3);
772 
773  logger.log("update best...",2);
774  bool updated_best = update_best(d);
775 
776  logger.log("calculate stats...",2);
777  calculate_stats(d);
778 
779  if (params.max_stall > 0)
780  update_stall_count(stall_count, updated_best);
781 
782  logger.log("update archive...",2);
783  if (use_arch)
784  archive.update(pop,params);
785 
786  if(params.verbosity>1)

858 void Feat::simplify_model(DataRef& d, Individual& ind)
859 {
860  /* Simplifies the final model using some expert rules and stochastic hill
861  * climbing.
862  * Expert rules:
863  * - NOT(NOT(x)) simplifies to x
864  * Stochastic hill climbing:
865  * for some number iterations, apply delete mutation to the equation.
866  * if the output of the model doesn't change, keep the mutations.
867  */
868 
870  // check for specific patterns
872  //
873  Individual tmp_ind = ind;
874  int starting_size = ind.size();
875  vector<size_t> roots = tmp_ind.program.roots();
876  vector<size_t> idx_to_remove;
877 
878  logger.log("\n=========\ndoing pattern pruning...",2);
879  logger.log("simplify: " + to_string(this->simplify), 2);
880 
881  for (auto r : roots)
882  {
883  /* cout << "r: " << r << "\n"; */
884  size_t start = tmp_ind.program.subtree(r);
885  int first_occurence = -2;
886 
887  /* cout << "start: " << start << "\n"; */
888  for (int i = start ; i <= r; ++i)
889  {
890  /* cout << "i: " << i << ", first_occurence: " << first_occurence */
891  /* << "\n"; */
892  if (tmp_ind.program.at(i)->name.compare("not")==0)
893  {
894  if (first_occurence == i-1) // indicates two NOTs in a row
895  {
896  /* cout << "pushing back " << first_occurence */
897  /* << " and " << i << " to idx_to_remove\n"; */
898  idx_to_remove.push_back(first_occurence);
899  idx_to_remove.push_back(i);
900  // reset first_occurence so we don't pick up triple nots
901  first_occurence = -2;
902  }
903  else
904  {
905  first_occurence = i;
906  }
907  }
908  }
909  }
910  // remove indices in reverse order so they don't change
911  std::reverse(idx_to_remove.begin(), idx_to_remove.end());
912  for (auto idx: idx_to_remove)
913  {
914  /* cout << "removing " << tmp_ind.program.at(idx)->name */
915  /* << " at " << idx << "\n"; */
916  tmp_ind.program.erase(tmp_ind.program.begin()+idx);
917  }
918  int end_size = tmp_ind.size();
919  logger.log("pattern pruning reduced best model size by "
920  + to_string(starting_size - end_size)
921  + " nodes\n=========\n", 2);
922  if (tmp_ind.size() < ind.size())
923  {
924  ind = tmp_ind;
925  logger.log("new model:" + this->get_eqn(false, ind),2);
926  }
927 
929  // prune dimensions
931  /* set_verbosity(3); */
932  int iterations = ind.get_dim();
933  logger.log("\n=========\ndoing correlation deletion mutations...",2);
934  starting_size = ind.size();
935  VectorXf original_yhat;
936  if (params.classification && params.n_classes==2)
937  original_yhat = ind.predict_proba(*d.o).row(0);
938  else
939  original_yhat = ind.yhat;
940 
941  for (int i = 0; i < iterations; ++i)
942  {
943  Individual tmp_ind = ind;
944  bool perfect_correlation = variator.correlation_delete_mutate(
945  tmp_ind, ind.Phi, params, *d.o);
946 
947  if (ind.size() == tmp_ind.size())
948  {
949  continue;
950  }
951 
952  tmp_ind.fit(*d.o, params);
953 
954  VectorXf new_yhat;
955  if (params.classification && params.n_classes==2)
956  new_yhat = tmp_ind.predict_proba(*d.o).row(0);
957  else
958  new_yhat = tmp_ind.yhat;
959 
960 
961  if (((original_yhat - new_yhat).norm()/original_yhat.norm()
962  <= this->simplify )
963  or perfect_correlation)
964  {
965  logger.log("\ndelete dimension mutation success: went from "
966  + to_string(ind.size()) + " to "
967  + to_string(tmp_ind.size()) + " nodes. Output changed by "
968  + to_string(100*(original_yhat
969  -new_yhat).norm()/(original_yhat.norm()))
970  + " %", 2);
971  if (perfect_correlation)
972  logger.log("perfect correlation",2);
973  ind = tmp_ind;
974  }
975  else
976  {
977  logger.log("\ndelete dimension mutation failure. Output changed by "
978  + to_string(100*(original_yhat
979  -new_yhat).norm()/(original_yhat.norm()))
980  + " %", 2);
981  // if this mutation fails, it will continue to fail since it
982  // is deterministic. so, break in this case.
983  break;
984  }
985 
986  }
987  end_size = ind.size();
988  logger.log("correlation pruning reduced best model size by "
989  + to_string(starting_size - end_size)
990  + " nodes\n=========\n", 2);
991  if (end_size < starting_size)
992  logger.log("new model:" + this->get_eqn(false, ind),2);
993 
995  // prune subtrees
997  iterations = 1000;
998  logger.log("\n=========\ndoing subtree deletion mutations...", 2);
999  starting_size = ind.size();
1000  for (int i = 0; i < iterations; ++i)
1001  {
1002  Individual tmp_ind = ind;
1003  this->variator.delete_mutate(tmp_ind, params);
1004  if (ind.size() == tmp_ind.size())
1005  continue;
1006 
1007  tmp_ind.fit(*d.o, params);
1008 
1009  VectorXf new_yhat;
1010  if (params.classification && params.n_classes==2)
1011  new_yhat = tmp_ind.predict_proba(*d.o).row(0);
1012  else
1013  new_yhat = tmp_ind.yhat;
1014 
1015  if ((original_yhat - new_yhat).norm()/original_yhat.norm()
1016  <= this->simplify )
1017  {
1018  logger.log("\ndelete mutation success: went from "
1019  + to_string(ind.size()) + " to "
1020  + to_string(tmp_ind.size()) + " nodes. Output changed by "
1021  + to_string(100*(original_yhat
1022  -new_yhat).norm()/(original_yhat.norm()))
1023  + " %", 2);
1024  ind = tmp_ind;
1025  }
1026  else
1027  {
1028  logger.log("\ndelete mutation failure. Output changed by "
1029  + to_string(100*(original_yhat
1030  -new_yhat).norm()/(original_yhat.norm()))
1031  + " %", 2);
1032  // if this mutation fails, it will continue to fail since it
1033  // is deterministic. so, break in this case.
1034  break;
1035  }
1036 
1037  }
1038  end_size = ind.size();
1039  logger.log("subtree deletion reduced best model size by "
1040  + to_string( starting_size - end_size )
1041  + " nodes", 2);
1042  VectorXf new_yhat;
1043  if (params.classification && params.n_classes==2)
1044  new_yhat = ind.predict_proba(*d.o).row(0);
1045  else
1046  new_yhat = ind.yhat;
1047  VectorXf difference = new_yhat - original_yhat;
1048  /* cout << "final % difference: " << difference.norm()/original_yhat.norm() */
1049  /* << endl; */
1050 }

1129  /* unsigned(d.t->Z.size())); */

1131

1135  // linear model to each feature in order to set initial weights

1148  else

1154 
1155  }

1161  {
1162  best_ind.program.push_back(params.terminals.at(i)->clone());
1163  }
1164  // if there is longitudinal data, initialize the model with median
1165  // values applied to those variables.
1166  for (unsigned i =0; i<n_z; ++i)
1167  {
1168  best_ind.program.push_back(params.terminals.at(n_x + i)->clone());
1169  best_ind.program.push_back(
1170  std::unique_ptr<Node>(new NodeMedian()));
1171  }
1172  }
1173  // fit model
1174 
1175  shared_ptr<CLabels> yhat;
1176 
1177

1182  else
1183  {

1186  yhat = best_ind.fit_tune(*d.t, params, true);
1187  else
1188  yhat = best_ind.fit(*d.t, params);
1189  // set terminal weights based on model
1190  vector<float> w = best_ind.ml->get_weights();
1191 
1192  params.set_term_weights(w);
1193  }
1194

1201  params.class_weights);
1202  }
1203  else
1204  this->min_loss_v = min_loss;
1205

1207 
1208  this->best_complexity = best_ind.get_complexity();
1209
